<p>I wasn‚Äôt building randomly.<br>
I was <strong>building what was already alive in my mind</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h2>I Build Because Only I Could Fill This Gap</h2>
<p>The most important part of my work is this:</p>
<p>I am not trying to copy anyone else‚Äôs structure.<br>
I am not trying to meet anyone else‚Äôs expectations.</p>
<p><strong>I am building structures uniquely suited to my own nature</strong>,<br>
because the gap I am filling in society is one that only I could fill.</p>
<p>I don‚Äôt need millions of voices to tell me I‚Äôm right.<br>
Reality itself will eventually prove that the scaffolding I built was necessary ‚Äî<br>
because I built it aligned with how emergence naturally unfolds.</p>
<p>I don‚Äôt build to be seen.<br>
